HEADWORD: Adjudicate
<hw>Ad*ju"di*cate</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Adjudicated</conjf>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Adjudicating</conjf>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>adjudicatus</ets>, p. p. of
<ets>adjudicare</ets>. See <er>Adjudge</er>.]</ety> <def>To adjudge; to
try and determine, as a court; to settle by judicial decree.</def>⟦br⟧
